notes:
Algeria has 3 levels of administrative boundaries: Admin level 0, Admin level 1, Admin Level 2. 
Admin 0 boundary refers to Algeria country boundary - Polygon, Admin 1 refers to Governorates - (Wilaya- province) -Polygon, and Admin 2 refers to district (Commune) -Polygon.
These data were extracted from the GADM database (www.gadm.org), version 2.8, November 2015. They can be used for non-commercial purposes only.
